The paper discusses the use of consumer wearable devices such as smartwatches to monitor heart rate variability (HRV) in everyday life. This topic falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it involves the interaction between humans and technology. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning to minimize errors in HRV measurements, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of sensor data, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of neural learning to minimize errors, which could fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
